A carboy should be easy to clean completely. I'd suspect the racking
cane or tubing. Both are cheap, you might consider replacing them.

Your brewing area might also have become home to this wild yeast (if
it really is a yeast). Maybe it's getting into your wort while it's
cooling, before you pitch the yeast. How are you doing that part?

