Sounds like a Brett infection to me.  The homebrew store is right, it's
tough to get rid of them.  They won't effect flavor unless you do long
term aging.  Eventually it'll start to have an impact, but as long as you're
not going to be sitting the bottles aside for several months you should
be fine.

I've gotten a couple Brett breakouts in the past.  What I did was to give
everything a good long soak in a bleach solution (IMO, make it stronger
than usual and let them soak for at least a day).  As far as the cheap stuff
like tubing, IMO it's best to throw it away and get new ones.  It's really
difficult to thoroughly clean tubing anyway.  Carboys, buckets, hydrometers,
etc should be fine with just a thorough bleaching.

John.
